   PEOPLES R CHINA, OCT 13-14, 2025},
Organization = {Chinese Optical Society},
Abstract = {Conventional optical device design methods are often inefficient,
   primarily because they struggle to connect with diverse user
   requirements, which leads to extended design periods, repeated
   adjustments to meet expectations, and failures to fully capture user
   demands, thereby hampering development efficiency and accuracy.To
   address these issues, OptiInverse generative pre-trained transformer is
   an artificial intelligence (AI) tool developed for the reverse design of
   optical devices. Being built on fine-tuning of the Qwen3 model, agent,
   along with retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) technologies, enhances
   the system's understanding of photonic device knowledge. This designed
   system can parse key details from users' inputs and provide relevant
   customized simulation and design codes, offering a flexible,
   user-friendly solution. It forms a robust pipeline that efficiently
   handles a variety of tasks, including forward prediction of transmission
   and reflection spectra, along with reverse design of optical structures.
   This work further explores the merits of integrating agent, RAG
   technologies, and deep learning frameworks in optical device design,
   underscoring its transformative potential for advancing related research
   and applications.},
