   and Horawalavithana, Sameera and Halappanavar, Mahantesh and Meyur,
   Rounak and Acharya, Anurag and Strube, Jan and Fierce, Laura},
Book-Group-Author = {ACM},
Title = {Leveraging Multimodal AI for Efficient Data Discovery in Wind Energy
   Research},
Booktitle = {PRACTICE AND EXPERIENCE IN ADVANCED RESEARCH COMPUTING 2025, PEARC 2025},
Year = {2025},
Note = {2025 Practice and Experience in Advanced Research Computing
   Conference-PEARC, Columbus, OH, JUL 20-24, 2025},
Organization = {Association for Computing Machinery},
Abstract = {Effective data discovery is crucial for driving progress in complex
   fields like wind energy research, where large volumes of scientific
   studies, environmental data, and regulatory documents need to be
   explored and synthesized. Traditional search methods, primarily based on
   keyword matching, often fail to provide precise results due to the
   fragmented nature of the data, which is distributed across various
   databases and presented in different formats such as text, images, maps,
   etc. This paper proposes an AI-driven framework designed to streamline
   the discovery and integration of wind energy-related data utilizing
   advanced multimodal techniques. This framework integrates data from the
   Tethys database, curating environmental and regulatory documents, and
   transforming them into a unified multimodal vector database. This system
   leverages Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to perform sophisticated
   multimodal search and generative chat applications. The proposed
   framework improves decision making in wind energy projects by enabling
   efficient access to both textual and visual information. Our results
   demonstrate how the AI capabilities of the system reduce time and effort
   in data discovery, offering a comprehensive tool for research, planning,
   and execution in the development of wind energy.},
