Note = {20th Conference of the Spanish Association for Artificial Intelligence
   (CAEPIA), A Coruna, SPAIN, JUN 19-21, 2024},
Abstract = {Suicide is a major health and social issue worldwide; therefore, a
   simple access to reliable sources of information that can be used by
   family members or friends of people who have suicidal ideation can be a
   valuable resource. This information can be provided by means of chatbot
   tools; however, the reliability and topicality of the chatbot's answers
   should be ensured. In this work, we present an architecture to build a
   chatbot with the aim of providing reliable suicide information in
   Spanish. The architecture consists of two text classification models
   (one to check that a user's question is related to suicidal content, and
   another to decide whether the user is looking for information or if the
   question should be derived to a human), and a retrieval augmented
   generation system that, using as a basis a corpus of documents filtered
   by experts, generates an answer to the user question. In addition, all
   the components of the architecture have been automatically tested to
   prove their suitability to be incorporated to the chatbot. The developed
   system is a step towards helping in one of the greatest global public
   health concerns.},
