Note = {26th International Symposium on Quality Electronic Design-ISQED-Annual,
   San Francisco, CA, APR 23-25, 2025},
Abstract = {The increasing complexity of integrated circuits (ICs) poses significant
   challenges for Electronic Design Automation (EDA) tools and users.
   Debugging EDA runtime issues can be time-consuming and frustrating due
   to complex error messages, extensive documentation, and limited
   knowledge sharing. Although open-source EDA tools like OpenROAD and
   OpenLane have democratized chip design, the dependence on expert
   knowledge and the prolonged response times for issue resolution remain
   significant obstacles. We introduce EDA-Debugger, a novel multi-agent
   Large Language Model (LLM) based framework for automated EDA runtime
   issue resolution to address these challenges. The EDA-Debugger uses the
   power of LLMs to analyze EDA log files, identify potential issues, and
   provide actionable solutions. By integrating EDA domain-specific
   Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG), EDA-Debugger bridges the gap
   between designers, LLMs, and EDA tools, enhancing efficiency and
   accessibility for users of all skill levels. Our evaluation of a
   benchmark dataset of 20 typical open-source EDA issues shows a 50\%
   improvement in issue resolution and 20.1\% improvement on average score
   compared to GPT-4 alone. This paper outlines the architecture,
   functionalities, and evaluation of EDA-Debugger, demonstrating its
   potential to revolutionize the EDA debugging process.},
